# MongoDB Docker Setup

## Installation

1. **Install Docker:** If you don't have Docker installed, download and install it from [Docker's official website](https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/).

2. **Run the Docker Compose Configuration:** Use the following command to start the MongoDB container using Docker Compose:

   ```bash
   docker-compose up -d
# Verify MongoDB
## Docker Dashboard: 
You can check the status of the MongoDB container in the Docker Dashboard or by running docker ps in your terminal.

## Access MongoDB: 
MongoDB will be accessible at localhost:27017.

# Stopping MongoDB
To stop and remove the MongoDB container, use the following command:
```
docker-compose down
